{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Rename \u2018BBC licence fee\u2019 to \u2018BBC subscription\u2019",
        "additional_details": "The general public has the legal freedom to purchase, as they see fit, broadcast media from any source. If that is subscriptions to a streaming service, it should never include the term 'licence' which may confuse the public into thinking there is a need or legal requirement to pay it when they neither watch BBC nor live TV.",
        "background": "We call on the Government to rename \u2018BBC license fee\u2019 to \u2018BBC subscription. The public must be in no doubt that payment to watch the BBC and live TV is voluntary and the word 'licence' implies a legal requirement, which is not the case if they are not watching BBC or live tv.",
